plement metric to demonstrate return on investment against the channel marketing investment. Manage the local Channel Marketing Budget Localise all partner-facing communications via multiple vehicles including newsletters, partner web portal, and print. Collaborate with Sales and Channel to streamline and time the delivery of “value-add” content to partners. Identify, define and deliver channel marketing tools and programs to assist the channel in generating leads, selling and closing deals. ·         Form strategic relationships and drive corporate brand awareness and demand through the partners. Evaluate and measure current processes, and where necessary, establish more efficient and consistent ones. Evangelize and champion channel mission, purpose, and needs internally. Skills/Experience Required: Understanding of competitors in the backup, recovery, and storage space Prior experience in a marketing manager role with a excellent understanding of channel marketing programs, especially those aimed at increasing channel engagement and sell-through. Excellent verbal and written communications skills; presentation, customer service, business, and negotiation skills. Strong interpersonal and collaboration skills. High energy with the capability to multi-task in a dynamic, rapidly growing organization. Ability to manage priorities and deadlines.   About this companyCommVaultCommVault Systems, Inc. provides data management software applications and related services. Commvault's Simpana software uses an expandable range of application modules, sharing a single set of back-end services, to deliver leading-edge functionality that truly unifies and simplifies enterprise data management and maximizes cost effectiveness. CommVault’s Simpana platform integrates backup and recovery, snapshot management and recovery, active data migration and archiving, data search and discovery, enterprise service level management and reporting, and storage resource management software solutions. The company sells software, and support and services to large global enterprises, small and medium sized businesses, and government agencies, both directly through its sales force and indirectly through its global network of value added resellers. It offers professional services, such as assessment and design services, implementation services, and system care review services, as well as training services. The company has strategic partnership with Dell, Hewlett-Packard, Hitachi Data Systems, Microsoft, Network Appliance, Novell, and Oracle. CommVault was founded in 1996 and is headquartered in Oceanport, New Jersey, with additional offices in the United States, Canada, Europe, Middle East, Africa, Mexico and Latin America, Asia-Pacific and India, and Oceania.Other jobs at CommVaultAustin, Texas AreaSingaporeGreater Atlanta AreaSimilar jobsSingaporePosted 4 days agoSingaporePosted 28 days agoSingaporePosted 19 days agoSingaporePosted 28 days agoSingaporePosted 14 days agoSingaporePosted 21 hours agoSingaporePosted 16 days agoSingaporePosted 20 days agoSan Francisco Bay AreaPosted 15 hours agoSan Francisco Bay AreaPosted 14 days agoThis is a preview of the Channel Marketing Manager - APAC job at CommVault. To view the full job listing, join LinkedIn - its free!Join LinkedIn - its free!People also searchedPeople also viewedSingaporePosted 4 days agoSingaporePosted 6 days agoSingaporePosted 21 hours agoSingaporePosted 7 days agoSingaporePosted 7 days agoSingaporePosted 8 days agoSingaporePosted 7 days agoSingaporePosted 20 days agoSingaporePosted 13 days agoSingaporePosted 4 days ago
